><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531189\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531189\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qby1665702990226.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qby1665702990226.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qby1665702990226.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qby1665702990226\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Printing to PostScript\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To print to PostScript, you need to define a print job model that uses the P_X11 translation table.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"qby1665702990226__context_w2410ab1b5b1_w2411ab1b5_w2412ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"qby1665702990226__topic_d65087e1_d65088e1_d65089e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qby1665702990226__p_d65090e1_d65091e1_d65092e1\">To print output to PostScript:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qby1665702990226__li_d28223e1_d28224e1_d28225e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Define a Print Job Model, setting the properties as follows:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__1\">\n Property\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__2\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Name</span>:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__2\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Name</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__3\">Enter a meaningful name, such as\n                                 <kbd class=\"ph userinput\">PS</kbd>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Device Type</span>:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">P_X11</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xiz1665702989085.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xiz1665702989085.html\" title=\"Printer device tables are a collection of sequences (control codes) associated with specific logical functions (such as bold, form feed, and init). The sequences begin with the escape character and are referred to as escape sequences.\">Device Translation Tables for Printing</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Print Queue</span>:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__2\">\n Blank, <var class=\"keyword varname\">BatchFile</var> or other process\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__3\">Leave this field blank to save the output\n                              as a PostScript file with the standard Uniface print file name <span class=\"ph filepath\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FormName</var>.P<var class=\"keyword varname\">nn</var></span>.\n                                 <p class=\"p\">Alternatively, specify a batch file or other print queue that\n                                 will be used to handle the output.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Top Margin</span>:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__2\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Lines</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qby1665702990226__table_d5702e1_d5703e1_d5704e1__entry__3\">\n Values for margins to position the output properly. A <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Top Margin</span> of at least 4 (lines) is recommended. (optional)\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qby1665702990226__li_d28226e1_d28227e1_d28228e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you require fonts that are not included in the standard set delivered with Uniface, copy the Adobe Font Metric files (<span class=\"ph filepath\">*.afm</span>) to the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/afm</span> directory.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qby1665702990226__li_d28229e1_d28230e1_d28231e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you want to change the fonts and sizes, edit the settings in the [postscript] section of <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span>.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nbh1665702675570.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define a Print Job Model</a><p>You must define a print job model before you can print data from Form components.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vsb1665702989292.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Initiating Printing</a><p>You initiate the print process from within Uniface using the Proc print command or the ^Print structure editor function.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eio1665702989590.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>PostScript Support</a><p>Uniface supports output to PostScript files. PostScript files can be directed to a third-party utility for printing or conversion to PDF. This is useful for batch PDF generation, but also provides enhanced printing capabilities on non-Windows platforms.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/giv1665702989665.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Font Support for PostScript Output</a><p>Font rendering for PostScript depends on the font files on your machine. Only Adobe PostScript Type 1 fonts are supported for PostScript printing.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yzq1665702989739.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>[postscript]</a><p>The [postscript] section of the initialization file defines logical fonts that override those used by default when printing to PostScript on Windows.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531189\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531189\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Printing to PostScript Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Printing to PostScript To print to PostScript, you need to define a print job model that uses the P_X11 translation table. To print output to PostScript: Define a Print Job Model, setting the properties as follows: Property Value Description Name : Name Enter a meaningful name, such as PS . Device Type : P_X11 For more information, see Device Translation Tables for Printing . Print Queue : Blank, BatchFile or other process Leave this field blank to save the output as a PostScript file with the standard Uniface print file name FormName .P nn . Alternatively, specify a batch file or other print queue that will be used to handle the output. Top Margin : Lines Values for margins to position the output properly. A Top Margin of at least 4 (lines) is recommended. (optional) If you require fonts that are not included in the standard set delivered with Uniface, copy the Adobe Font Metric files ( *.afm ) to the /common/afm directory. If you want to change the fonts and sizes, edit the settings in the [postscript] section of usys.ini . Related Links Define a Print Job Model You must define a print job model before you can print data from Form components. Initiating Printing You initiate the print process from within Uniface using the Proc print command or the ^Print structure editor function. PostScript Support Uniface supports output to PostScript files. PostScript files can be directed to a third-party utility for printing or conversion to PDF. This is useful for batch PDF generation, but also provides enhanced printing capabilities on non-Windows platforms. Font Support for PostScript Output Font rendering for PostScript depends on the font files on your machine. Only Adobe PostScript Type 1 fonts are supported for PostScript printing. [postscript] The [postscript] section of the initialization file defines logical fonts that override those used by default when printing to PostScript on Windows. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}